    "description": "MobiKwik Consulting Pvt Ltd is actively seeking a talented and motivated Financial Analyst to join our dynamic team in Noida. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout MobiKwik Consulting Pvt Ltd:\nMobiKwik Consulting Pvt Ltd is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Conduct due diligence for mergers, acquisitions, and investments\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in Bloomberg Terminal\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Noida, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with MobiKwik Consulting Pvt Ltd!",
